TEST PLAN


Our testing strategy was to build and test incrementally, verifying each
feature before moving on to the next. We tested both interactive and
batch modes for each scenario.

1. Basic command execution
   - Tested: echo hello, ls, pwd
   - How: ran ./mysh in interactive mode, verified correct output

2. Batch mode (file argument)
   - Tested: ./mysh myscript.sh where myscript.sh contains "echo hello"
   - How: verified "hello" printed with no prompts or welcome message

3. Batch mode (stdin pipe)
   - Tested: echo "echo hello" | ./mysh
   - How: verified "hello" printed with no prompts

4. Interactive mode messages and prompt
   - Tested: welcome message on startup, goodbye on exit, prompt format
   - How: ran ./mysh manually, checked "Welcome to my shell!" printed,
     prompt shows current directory with ~ for home prefix,
     "Exiting my shell" printed on exit

5. Built-in: cd
   - Tested: cd (no args goes to HOME), cd subdir, cd /tmp,
     cd nonexistent (error), cd a b (too many args)
   - How: checked prompt updated after cd, error message on failure

6. Built-in: pwd
   - Tested: pwd output, pwd > out.txt (redirection)
   - How: compared output to actual working directory

7. Built-in: which
   - Tested: which ls, which echo, which cd (built-in, should fail),
     which fakeprog (not found, should fail)
   - How: verified correct path printed, nothing printed on failure

8. External command with path
   - Tested: /bin/ls, ./mysh (nested shell)
   - How: verified correct execution

9. Unknown command
   - Tested: fakecommand
   - How: verified error message printed, shell continues

10. Input redirection
    - Tested: cat < file.txt
    - How: verified file contents printed to stdout

11. Output redirection
    - Tested: echo hello > out.txt
    - How: verified file created with correct contents

12. Both redirections
    - Tested: cat < in.txt > out.txt, also in reverse order (> before <)
    - How: verified both orderings work identically

13. Redirection error
    - Tested: cat < nonexistent.txt
    - How: verified error message printed, shell continues

14. Pipes (two processes)
    - Tested: ls | grep mysh, echo hello | cat
    - How: verified output flows correctly between processes

15. Pipes (three or more processes)
    - Tested: ls | cat | cat, echo hello | cat | cat | cat
    - How: verified full pipeline output is correct

16. Wildcards (match)
    - Tested: echo *.c, ls *.c
    - How: verified tokens expanded to matching filenames

17. Wildcards (no match)
    - Tested: echo *.xyz
    - How: verified token passed through unchanged as "*.xyz"

18. Wildcards (hidden files)
    - Tested: echo *.txt where .hidden.txt exists
    - How: verified .hidden.txt not included in matches

19. Wildcards (path prefix)
    - Tested: echo subdir/*.c
    - How: verified files in subdirectory expanded correctly

20. Comments
    - Tested: echo hello # this is a comment
    - How: verified only "hello" printed, comment ignored

21. Empty line
    - Tested: pressing enter on blank line
    - How: verified shell does nothing and reprints prompt

22. Exit status reporting (interactive mode)
    - Tested: false (exits with status 1)
    - How: verified "Exited with status 1" printed before next prompt

23. Signal termination reporting (interactive mode)
    - Tested: a program killed by SIGKILL
    - How: verified "Terminated by signal X" printed with signal description

24. Exit command
    - Tested: exit, also foo | exit
    - How: verified shell terminates after current job completes

25. Syntax errors
    - Tested: < <, > (no filename following)
    - How: verified error printed, shell skips to next command
